HEADWORD: Furuncle
<hw>Fu"run*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>furunculus</ets> a petty thief, a boil, dim. of <ets>fur</ets>
thief: cf. F. <ets>furoncle</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
superficial, inflammatory tumor, suppurating with a central core; a
boil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

